3. 養聲
廣東話：歌手喺演唱會之前要靜養聲，唔好講太多說話。
English: The singer needs to rest his voice before the concert and shouldn't talk too much.

4. 票尾
廣東話：我將張車票嘅票尾搣落嚟，留低做收據。
English: I tore off the stub of the train ticket and kept it as a receipt.

5. hacker
廣東話：個 hacker 試圖入侵銀行嘅系統，但最後被保安捉咗。
English: The hacker tried to breach the bank's system but was eventually caught by security.

6. 石斛蘭
廣東話：公園入面種咗好多石斛蘭，佢哋好鍾意依附喺大樹上面生長。
English: There are many Dendrobium orchids planted in the park; they love growing by clinging to large trees.

7. 吊詭 (矛盾、悖論)
廣東話：呢個邏輯問題真係好吊詭，點解越解釋越混亂？
English: This logical problem is truly paradoxical; why does it get more confusing the more you explain it?

8. 吊詭 (似非而是、荒謬)
廣東話：佢話自己好窮，但係成日買名牌手袋，真係好吊詭。
English: He says he's very poor, but he keeps buying designer handbags; it's truly absurd.

9. 各為其主
廣東話：雖然佢哋係好朋友，但因為各為其主，最後都變成對手。
English: Although they were good friends, because each acted for their own master, they eventually became rivals.

10. 軨蓋
廣東話：佢開車嘅時候，軨蓋突然彈起，好危險。
English: When he was driving, the car hood suddenly popped up, which was very dangerous.

11. 打哥夫
廣東話：佢週末好鍾意同幾個老友去高爾夫球場打哥夫。
English: He likes to go to the golf course with a few old friends to play golf on weekends.

12. 免揀
廣東話：呢間餐廳嘅套餐係免揀嘅，你唔可以隨意選擇菜式。
English: The set menu at this restaurant is non-selectable; you cannot choose dishes freely.

13. 擺闊佬
廣東話：佢新買咗部豪車，成日想擺闊佬畀人睇。
English: He just bought a luxury car and always wants to show off his wealth to others.

14. 廣播劇
廣東話：我成日喺放工路上聽廣播劇，好過癮。
English: I often listen to radio dramas on my way home from work; it's very enjoyable.

15. 錄影機
廣東話：舊時好多人用錄影機錄電視節目，而家就少人用啦。
English: In the past, many people used VCRs to record TV programs, but nowadays few do.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩
廣東話：佢喺場上唱錯咗歌詞，但係證據確鑿，真係吟詩吟唔甩。
English: He sang the wrong lyrics on stage, but the evidence is undeniable; he simply cannot deny it.

17. 佈道大會
廣東話：教會下個月會舉辦一場大型嘅佈道大會，歡迎大家參加。
English: The church will hold a large evangelism conference next month; everyone is welcome to attend.

18. 寫手 (寫作的人)
廣東話：佢係一名專業寫手，專門為雜誌撰寫專欄文章。
English: He is a professional writer who specializes in writing columns for magazines.

19. 寫手 (代替他人寫作的人)
廣東話：有啲學生唔識寫論文，就搵寫手幫佢哋代寫。
English: Some students who can't write their theses hire ghostwriters to write them for them.

20. 代打
廣東話：我今日唔得閒，可以唔可以請你幫我代打幾局遊戲？
English: I'm busy today; can you help me play a few rounds of the game for me?

21. 茶碗
廣東話：佢好鍾意收藏日本嘅茶碗，每隻都好精緻。
English: He loves collecting Japanese tea bowls; each one is very exquisite.

22. 茶隔
廣東話：沖茶嘅時候，記得將茶隔放喺茶杯上面，先將茶葉同茶湯分開。
English: When brewing tea, remember to place the tea strainer on top of the cup to separate the tea leaves from the tea soup.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈
廣東話：公司只許老闆遲到，唔准員工遲到，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。
English: The company allows the boss to be late but forbids employees from being late; it's truly "only the magistrate can set fires, but commoners are not allowed to light lamps."

24. 獨唱
廣東話：今晚嘅演唱會，佢會獨自一人上台獨唱一首歌。
English: Tonight's concert, he will go on stage alone to sing a song solo.

25. 快人快事
廣東話：佢係個快人快事嘅人，有咩問題就直接講，唔會拖泥帶水。
English: He is a straightforward person; if there's a problem, he speaks directly without dragging things out.

26. 四腳獸
廣東話：有啲人喺公廁入面做啲唔該死嘅事，被稱為四腳獸。
English: Some people do inappropriate things in the public restroom and are referred to as "four-legged beasts."

27. 無米粥
廣東話：我哋今日只係去同對方傾下無米粥，具體細節仲未確定。
English: We just went for an initial discussion today; the specific details are not yet confirmed.

28. 義會
廣東話：以前窮人冇錢借錢，就靠義會互相幫助，解決燃眉之急。
English: In the past, poor people had no money to borrow, so they relied on rotating credit associations to help each other and solve urgent financial needs.

29. 榜文
廣東話：古代嘅皇帝會貼出榜文，宣佈重要嘅政令。
English: Ancient emperors would post edicts to announce important government decrees.

30. MK名
廣東話：佢個網名係一個典型嘅 MK 名，充滿咗奇怪嘅符號同字頭。
English: His online username is a typical MK name, filled with strange symbols and prefixes. [end of text]


